{
  "stem": "7458.1",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 1.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "However, as I will probably have a chance to discuss later, everyone worked so hard that it was very difficult to find time to pray on a daily basis.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But certainly holidays and Shabbat was observed very closely.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "My father owned a [? tannery ?].",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "When I was born, he actually worked for someone.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And we lived in a very small house in the center of town.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Eventually, my father bought a tannery and employed other people.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Excuse me.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "[DRINKS]",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Let me take perhaps a segment of time and, in my own words, describe Jasionovka and the home I lived in.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Jasionovka was a little town, like thousands and thousands of other towns in Eastern Europe, in the Pale of Settlement.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "In Yiddish, it was called shtetl.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And I think it was the Jewish author Sholem Aleichem who once described-- he said, if you want to know what the map of Eastern Europe looked like and the shtetlach, he says, consider a Friday night challah with poppy seeds sprinkled all over.",
      "word_count": 44
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "That's how those towns were sprinkled over Eastern Europe.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And Jasionovka was one of those little towns.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "There were approximately 2,000 people who lived in the town.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Most of them were Jewish.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "There were a few non-Jews.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Of course, like all the other towns, we were surrounded by villages which were completely occupied by Polish-- Polish farmers.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "Jasionovka had no electricity, no paved streets.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "The homes were not much more than huts, many of them with dirt floors, some of them with wooden floors.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "We had no running water.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "Water had to be carried from a well.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "Wood had to be chopped and brought in, in order to heat and cook with.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And life was extremely hard.",
      "word_count": 5
    }
  ],
